A group of local fitness locations here in Berkley put together a fundraiser last month for Berkley athletics. I was not able to attend due to personal reasons. Thank you for all those who hosted and participated! We raised over $700 for the athletics program. Not bad! We have a long way to get our athletics where they need to be!

For the rest of the year my goal is to have our records updated and visible. Also, they have not been updated in over 20 years😳😳. Needless to say, records have been broke in that time. It’s unfortunate that if you break a record you don’t get your name on the record board. The boys mile record was broke this year. Sucks he doesn’t know when he’ll see his name.

I don’t know of anyone where else that this isn’t updated yearly!

@anytimefitnessberkley we will be running fundraising group classes starting August 30th. All money will go to updating the records and making them visible. If you sign up for personal training with me as a new member. Half of the training package you pick will go to the fundraiser as well. @jaredmpurcell is working on putting together more fundraisers.

A quick and effective leg workout. Great for after a run!

✅Squats 
✅Reverse Lunges
✅Jump Squats

Short and sweet! You can do these before your run to warm up or even during your run to help get loose.

You can’t run and be strong. Is one of my favorite myths about running. You can definitely do both! It takes a lot of time, dedication and effort. Which is not easy! For me my main focuses

✅Not to miss a run or lift. You need to have the time for both!

✅Find the right program! Message me to sign up for my program!

✅Calorie surplus. You have to get enough protein and carbs and then you have to get even more!

✅Creatine! I really focus on getting my creatine after my lifting session. It is essential for muscle recovery.

Let’s work together!

Show up with a plan! Your workout will be more efficient! If you can’t come up with a plan. Hit me up to help get your started with your plan!
